<a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/btrinityalliance>Trinity Alliance</a>, Prexus<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#DDDDAA><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvydas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vydas</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>3/22/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>11:23:59 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Server Side Filtering on Test - Film at 11</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I'm concerned about healer updates, too, but please note that the latter portion of this includes making the periodic update more frequent than the current 6 seconds.  The whole post isn't too specific about what actually is being done on test <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#AADDDD><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvinreagc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vinrea GC</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalRainbow.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>3/22/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>11:24:37 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Server Side Filtering on Test - Film at 11</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">That's not exactly it Ello..<br>
<br>
Every six seconds you recieve a update of all the health info of everything in your aggro circle and group members if they are in zone. This is directly from the server. As you fight you see the &quot;ATank gets hit for 125 damage&quot; message and <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> YOUR</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> pc does a little math and subtracts 125HP from ATanks red bar. Now this in not neccessarily 100% accurate, but it is usually close and will be corrected if wrong by the six scond update.<br>
<br>
If you filter out these messages, as most casters do, right now it doesn't matter. Because your computer is still recieving them, it is just not displaying the text. So while you don't see &quot;ATank gets hit for 125 damage&quot; your computer did see it and your computer still does the math.<br>
<br>
This however causes a ton of traffic to your PC. If you filter everything from the server the info is never actually sent. So you still don't see the hit message, but your PC does not know the ATank got hit for 125 damage and therefore cannot do the math to show you this hit on his health bar. You have to wait for the six second update to come through before you see any change.<br>
<br>
This would be a bad thing for clerics trying to time a CH or really anyone healing at all. Plus since it affects the mob too it would end up causing casters to nuke alot of dead bodies. I think if they sped up the HP refresh for group and target it would help alot, but that might defeat the whole purpose of the change.. hummm.<br>
</font><P>Vinrea 51 Heretic<BR>
