Prexus Server<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#DDDDAA><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umolex.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Molex</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>3/22/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>11:26:34 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Server Side Filtering on Test - Film at 11</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Client side filter does nothing more than hiding all the information that's coming in to your client. It's all still coming in, thus creating the lag. You just don't get to see it if you filter client side. <br>
<br>
